'''Malika''' ([[Arabic language|Arabic]]: مللك)  means [[Queen]] in Arabic. It is the female version of the word [[Malik]] that means "King" in [[Arabic language|Arabic]]  Thus, Malika means [[monarch|Queen]].  This terminology has been adopted into numerous other languages, including [[Persian language|Persian]]  and [[Urdu language|Urdu]], where it is pronounced "Malekeh". It is derived from the word [[Malak]] which means 'angel'.

Malika is a common [[Muslim girls name in [[Pakistan]]. Malika [[Devanagari]]: मलीका) is also commonly a name for girls in [[India]].


